    },
    {
        "Old Polish Language": "Old Polish Language"
    },
    {
        ". Little is known about this period of his life, other than that he moved out of his parents home, tutored part-time, and lived in poverty. His situation improved somewhat in 1868 when he became tutor to the princely Woroniecki family.     In 1867 he wrote a rhymed piece, Sielanka Młodości , which was rejected by  Tygodnik Ilustrowany  . In 1869 he debuted as a journalist; Przegląd Tygodniowy ran his review of a play on 18 April 1869, and shortly afterward The Illustrated Weekly printed an essay of his about the late-Renaissance Polish poet ": null
    },
    {
